A housekeeper was kidnapped, beaten and burned by her employers for eight hours after they accused her of stealing money and jewelry, reports claim.

Daisy Machuea, 54, was attacked as soon as she arrived at work in Queens, New York City, on February 13, police said.

Her employers, Devanand Lachman, 32, and his pregnant wife Ambar Lachman, 31, have been charged with felony assault, felony kidnapping and unlawful imprisonment.

