Machuea told NBC New York that Devanand Lachman and another man, who remains at large, burned her with a plumber's torch and beat her with a blunt object. 

Once Ambar Lachman arrived, she says, the group then allegedly drove her to Machuea's house while holding her at knifepoint and tore apart the property.

Her friend and housemate Oscar Ramirez said he was watching TV when the suspects arrived and told him: 'If you move, the other guy will kill her,' before stealing their cell phones.

